{"type":"data","nodes":[null,{"type":"data","data":[{"html":1,"frontmatter":2,"date":13,"lang":14,"tocData":15},"\u003Cp>\u003Ca href=\"https://github.com/folke/lazy.nvim\">\u003Cem>lazy.nvim\u003C/em>\u003C/a> is one of neovim plugin managers that helps you install plugins.\nBy specifying Github repositories or local directories,\nyou can install designated plugins easily.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cpre class=\"language-lua\">\u003Ccode class=\"language-lua code-highlight\">\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"1\">  \u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">{\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"2\">    \u003Cspan class=\"token string\">'nvim-lualine/lualine.nvim'\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">,\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"3\">    dependencies \u003Cspan class=\"token operator\">=\u003C/span> \u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">{\u003C/span> \u003Cspan class=\"token string\">'nvim-tree/nvim-web-devicons'\u003C/span> \u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">}\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">,\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"4\">    config \u003Cspan class=\"token operator\">=\u003C/span> \u003Cspan class=\"token keyword\">function\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">(\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">)\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"5\">      \u003Cspan class=\"token function\">require\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">(\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token string\">'lualine'\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">)\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">.\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token function\">setup\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">(\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">)\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"6\">    \u003Cspan class=\"token keyword\">end\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"7\">  \u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">}\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\n\u003Cp>This code installs and setups \u003Ca href=\"https://github.com/nvim-lualine/lualine.nvim\">lualine\u003C/a> from Github repository.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>But there are some repositories which host neovim plugin files in subdirectory\nfor some reasons such as to make the plugins available to programs other than neovim.\nIn that case you need to tell your plugin manager to look for the plugin in subdirectories.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>With \u003Ca href=\"https://github.com/VundleVim/Vundle.vim\">\u003Cem>Vundle\u003C/em>\u003C/a> plugin manager, you can easily do that with \u003Ccode>rtp\u003C/code> property.\nIt stands for 'runtimepath' and specifies the subdirectory that contains vim plugin files.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cpre class=\"language-lua\">\u003Ccode class=\"language-lua code-highlight\">\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"1\">Bundle \u003Cspan class=\"token string\">'sonph/onehalf'\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">,\u003C/span> \u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">{\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token string\">'rtp'\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">:\u003C/span> \u003Cspan class=\"token string\">'vim/'\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">}\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"2\">colorscheme onehalflight\n\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\n\u003Cp>The code above installs \u003Ca href=\"https://github.com/sonph/onehalf\">onehalf\u003C/a> colorscheme on your vim.\nBut lazy.nvim does not provide the same property in the plugin spec as of March 2024.\nSo how can you do that? Well, you can do the same with little bits of code.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cpre class=\"language-lua\">\u003Ccode class=\"language-lua code-highlight\">\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"1\">  \u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">{\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"2\">    \u003Cspan class=\"token string\">'sonph/onehalf'\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">,\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"3\">    config \u003Cspan class=\"token operator\">=\u003C/span> \u003Cspan class=\"token keyword\">function\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">(\u003C/span>plugin\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">)\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"4\">      vim\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">.\u003C/span>opt\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">.\u003C/span>rtp\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token function\">append\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">(\u003C/span>plugin\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">.\u003C/span>dir \u003Cspan class=\"token operator\">..\u003C/span> \u003Cspan class=\"token string\">\"/vim\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">)\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"5\">      vim\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">.\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token function\">cmd\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">(\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token string\">'colorscheme onehalflight'\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">)\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"6\">    \u003Cspan class=\"token keyword\">end\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"code-line line-number\" line=\"7\">  \u003Cspan class=\"token punctuation\">}\u003C/span>\n\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\n\u003Cp>In the config function, you receive the plugin as the parameter.\n\u003Ccode>..\u003C/code> is an operator in lua that concatenates the two adjacent strings.\nSo you are appending the exact subdirectory to the runtimepath with \u003Ccode>vim.opt.rtp:append\u003C/code> function.\nCheck out this issue link for more information: \u003Ca href=\"https://github.com/folke/lazy.nvim/issues/183\">https://github.com/folke/lazy.nvim/issues/183\u003C/a>\u003C/p>",{"layout":3,"toc":4,"title":5,"category":6,"tags":8,"author":11},"post",true,"How to Install Plugin from Subdirectory with lazy.nvim Plugin Manger",[7],"Programming",[9,10],"neovim","vim",[12],"이현재","2024-03-22","en",[]],"uses":{"params":["year","slug"]}}]}
